  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">ISA - Research and Monitoring Programme of Protected Indigenous Areas</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to guarantee the constitutional rights of indigenous people, via &#x2018;Research and Monitoring of Protected Areas and the Analysis and Dissemination of reliable information about indigenous people and their lands in Brazil.&#x2019;

In the context of growing threats to indigenous rights, and the use of and access to their lands, indigenous programme partners increasingly require ISA&#x2019;s (Instituto SocioAmbiental) support to research and monitor socio-environmental and legal changes related to their lands and rights. Through research, distribution and documentation of socio-environmental information and institutional strengthening of local partners, ISA intends to achieve the following outcomes: 

1. Brazilian society with access to qualified information about the cultural diversity of indigenous peoples and their lands in Brazil
2. Indigenous communities and organisations use the database on indigenous lands to support land development and environmental management.
3. Monitoring system with environmental indicators of indigenous lands in Brazil established and accessible to indigenous communities and partners.</narrative>
  </description>
